Within Active Object, if you build a Query.select() and use it with ao.stream() the number of entries returned is correct but all the fields within the proxy are null.  You can work around this using Query.select("*") to properly populate  your objects.   However, if you use the same Query.select("*") on ao.find() then HSQL throws the following error...

java.sql.SQLException: Column not found: *

This is an issue when trying to build a generic query builder and in some cases it goes to stream and others it goes to find.

