The editor loader has two mechanisms for loading the JS it needs. If the batch list includes only a single file (as it is normally) jQuery ajax is used with type "script". In the case there is more than one file, script tags are dynamically inserted in the head.

The ajax settings specified for the jQuery.ajax call are as follows

{code}
      var ajaxSettings = {
           dataType: "script",
           error: loadErrorCallback,
           success: loadCallback
       };
{code}

Per the jQuery docs, jQuery.ajax calls that specify a type of "script" are by default uncached (a _=\[TIMESTAMP\] url param is added) unless {{cache:true}} is specified. Adding that param should cache that file by default.

