When creating an active objects with a field of type java.util.Date and using a Derby database the database table creation fails. Derby supports DATE, TIME, and TIMESTAMP type and the active objects implementation uses DATETYPE as date type mapping for date (which does not exists!).

 The bug is located in class net.java.ao.types.TypeManager in function derby().

Here is an example of active object class which cannot be correctly generated.

package com.arhs.jaspers.confluence.plugin.model;

import java.util.Date;

import net.java.ao.Entity;

public interface BaseModel extends Entity {

	public Date getModificationDate();

	public void setModificationDate(Date modificationDate);

}

